organic_results.title: Social class, parental interest and the educational plans of American and Norwegian rural youth
organic_results.snippet: Taking into account the differences in societal context and system of educational tracking, this paper explores the interrelated influences of social class origins and parental interest on the educational plans of American high school and Norwegian ungdomsskole students. Data were obtained from 1396 Norwegian and 2313 Kentucky-West Virginia graduating seniors with the American phase focusing on college plans and the Norwegian on gymnas plans.
